title: Flight Simulator 2020 - POI's - Canada - Canadian High Arctic Research Station
description:
In this video we will fly over the Canadian High Arctic Research Station. Cambridge Bay  is a hamlet located on Victoria Island in the Kitikmeot Region of Nunavut, Canada. It is the largest settlement on Victoria Island. Cambridge Bay is named for Prince Adolphus, Duke of Cambridge, while the traditional Inuinnaqtun name for the area is Ikaluktutiak (old orthography) or Iqaluktuuttiaq (new orthography) meaning "good fishing place".
